Description

Two important things in this PR:

  1. Add dale-cli package
  2. Move all packages to packages folder, this is better to organize all packages and not having a lot of things in the root of the project. Also, when we migrate to Lerna it will be okay because Lerna uses this structure (I've being inspired by them). Keep in mind that approving this PR we'll have to do a small change in the packages builds/releases of the pkg.typescript becasue the path will be different.

To test dale-cli you need to run the binary:

$ bin/run

To run a command:

$ bin/run <command>

The build for this project will run uni tests and will publish this package to our artifacts. But I will config the build after the merge of this PR.

After being published, we can install in different project:

$ npm install -g @payvision/dale-cli
$ dale <command>

      export abstract class BaseError extends Error {
        source: string;
        constructor(
          code: number,
          message: string,
          details: any,
          data: any,
          source: string = 'Unknown',
        ) {
          super(message);
          this.code = code;
          this.details = details;
          this.data = data;
          this.source = source;
          this.name = this.constructor.name;
        }
      }
